news.title: Union cabinet approves Rithala-Kundli corridor for Delhi metro's phase-IV project
news.para: This line will be an extension of the operational Shaheed Sthal (New Bus Adda)-Rithala (Red Line) corridor and will boost connectivity in the northwestern parts of Delhi, such as Narela, Bawana and parts of Rohini.

news.title: Karnataka cabinet approves Bengaluru metro's phase 3A line from Sarjapur to Hebbal
news.para: The 36.6km line will have an elevated corridor of 22.1km with 17 stations and a 14.5km underground stretch with 11 stations.

news.title: No NOC for land transfers without approvals: Goa TCP department
news.para: To register a sale deed or change in ownership rights of a plot of land, a certificate of approval or an NOC from the TCP department is required if such a plot lacks permissions for sub-division or development. But there are exceptions to this rule.

news.title: Allahabad HC quashes Noida authority’s sealing of towers in Lotus Zing
news.para: The order was delivered by a division bench of justices Manoj Kumar Gupta and Anish Kumar Gupta on Dec 3. Three C Projects, the developer, argued before the court that Noida's move to seal the towers was "mechanical and illegal" and had caused irreparable harm.

news.title: CCI sends notice to UltraTech Cement for its proposed acquisition of India Cements
news.para: The notice is under the Section 29 (1) of the Competition Act, and is generally sent if the Commission is of the opinion that the proposed merger is likely to have or has had an adverse impact on competition.

news.title: Register flats under Uttar Pradesh's rehabilitation package by Dec 31: Greater Noida authority
news.para: Greater Noida Authority officials said it may revoke the benefits extended under the rehabilitation package for stalled projects — waiver of interests and penal interests accrued during the two Covid years — if developers missed the deadline.

news.title: Gurugram: Consumer forum orders Deluris Buildtech to compensate buyer for delay
news.para: The order was passed in a case of delayed handover to a homebuyer of Zara Rossa project in Sector 112.

news.title: Bengaluru: Infosys founder buys flat for 50 crore in Kingfisher Towers
news.para: The four-bedroom luxurious residence on the 16th floor spans approximately 8,400sqft. It comes with five designated car park spaces.

news.title: Gurugram: Buyers allege harassment and non-compliance by builders
news.para: Buyers have alleged that builders have been charging them higher interests, blaming them for the delay in the project, even threatening them with cancelling their allotments.

news.title: Info-x buys penthouse for Rs 190 crore in Gurugram's DLF Camellias
news.para: The deal was registered on December 2, and the company paid ₹13 crore stamp duty for the transaction, showed documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm.

news.title: NCLAT junks Jaiprakash Associates' plea against insolvency
news.para: ​While upholding an earlier order, the appellate tribunal NCLAT observed mere pending of loan restructuring arrangement with the lender before NCLT does not debar the creditors to file insolvency proceedings under section 7 of Insolvency & Bankruptcy Code 2016.

news.title: High court restrains eviction of 130 residents for expansion of Madurai airport
news.para: A division bench of justice M S Ramesh and justice A D Maria Clete passed the interim order while hearing a petition filed by P Malairajan and 129 other residents of Chinna Udaippu village. The judges sought a response from the state and adjourned the hearing to Dec 19.

news.title: China aims to boost foreign investment in property insurance market
news.para: The country will support qualified foreign financial institutions to invest in its property insurance market, and encourage domestic property insurance companies to optimise their offshore expansion, the statement said.

news.title: Pick up in cement demand expected in Q4 FY25: Ind-Ra
news.para: The demand for cement grew only by 2-3% in the H1 FY25, with construction affected by the elections and weather conditions.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC's environment department issues SOP to staff for monitoring anti-dust rules
news.para: The SOP details the steps that the sub-engineers need to take while visiting construction sites. BMC has asked contractors of infrastructure projects to submit an environment management plan (EMP) for projects.

news.title: Pilibhit DPRO refuses to take action in housing scam under Mukhyamantri awas yojana
news.para: Locals had earlier alleged they were coerced into paying bribes of Rs 10,000 each to secure housing under Mukhyamantri Awas Yojana, a govt scheme in UP.

news.title: House prices in UK rise 1.3% in November 2024: Halifax
news.para: House prices rose by 1.3% in monthly terms in November after an upwardly revised 0.4% increase in October to reach a new record of 298,083 pounds ($380,324) - well above a 0.2% rise predicted by economists in a Reuters poll.

news.title: Benaulim villagers oppose GTDC's hotel project on ecologically sensitive land
news.para: Villagers warned that moves to keep the panchayat in the dark while drawing up agreements with private parties does not sit well with locals, and if the hotel proposal moves forward, they will be forced to protest.

news.title: SC allows CAQM to relax GRAP-4 curbs in Delhi-NCR
news.para: A bench of Justices Abhay S Oka and Augustine George Masih, however, suggested the CAQM to include some additional measures of GRAP-3 in stage-2 curbs.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt submits modified DPR for Noida metro's aqua line extension to Centre
news.para: ​​ The modified DPR for the Rs 2,991.60 crore project was recently approved by the Uttar Pradesh Cabinet, said Lokesh M, Managing Director of the Noida Metro Rail Corporation (NMRC).
